ustomVerifyCertChainForQuic() for QUIC-specific validation\n   - customVerifyCallback() as the OpenSSL verify callback for custom validation\n   - Integration with CertValidatorPtr for pluggable validators\n\n5. **ServerContextImpl and ClientContextImpl** (source/common/tls/server_context_impl.h/.cc and client_context_impl.h/.cc): Server and client specific context implementations extending ContextImpl, with server context managing OCSP stapling decisions via ocspStapleAction().\n\n6. **OCSP Response Parsing and Stapling** (source/common/tls/ocsp/ocsp.h and .cc):\n   - OcspResponseWrapperImpl: Wraps DER-encoded OCSP responses, created via OcspResponseWrapperImpl::create()\n   - OcspResponse and BasicOcspResponse: ASN.1 structures for OCSP responses per RFC 6960\n   - SingleResponse and ResponseData: Structures for individual certificate status information\n   - Asn1OcspUtility: Parsing utilities for DER-encoded OCSP structures including parseOcspResponse(), parseBasicOcspResponse(), parseResponseData(), parseSingleResponse()\n   - readDerEncodedOcspResponse() and validateResponse() functions handle OCSP response parsing and validation\n   - OcspResponseStatus enum for handling OCSP response statuses (Successful, MalformedRequest, InternalError, TryLater, SigRequired, Unauthorized)\n\n7. **ASN.1 Parsing Utilities** (source/common/tls/ocsp/asn1_utility.h and .cc): Low-level ASN.1 DER parsing functions supporting OCSP-specific structures.\n\n8. **SPIFFEValidator** (source/extensions/transport_sockets/tls/cert_validator/spiffe/spiffe_validator.h and .cc): An alternative certificate validator implementing SPIFFE/SVID validation with its own matchSubjectAltName() method for SPIFFE certificate validation.\n\n9. **Certificate Factory Pattern** (source/common/tls/cert_validator/factory.h and .cc): CertValidatorFactory interface for registering and creating validator instances, with DefaultCertValidatorFactory as the primary implementation.\n\nThe validation chain flows as follows: SSL handshake → customVerifyCallback() → ContextImpl::customVerifyCertChain() → CertValidator::doVerifyCertChain() → DefaultCertValidator certificate verification methods (including SAN matching via san_matcher.cc) → OCSP validation (if configured) via OcspResponseWrapperImpl. The pipeline supports both synchronous and asynchronous validation, certificate pinning, OCSP stapling, and extensible SAN matching strategies."
